<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc0190883-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16523"><num value="16523">§ 16523.</num><heading> Alaska natural gas pipeline</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than 180 days after <date date="2005-08-08">August 8, 2005</date>, and every 180 days thereafter until the Alaska natural gas pipeline commences operation, the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission shall submit to Congress a report describing—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc0190884-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16523/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the progress made in licensing and constructing the pipeline; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc0190885-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s16523/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> any issue impeding that progress.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idc0190886-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/58/tXVIII/s1810">Pub. L. 109–58, title XVIII, § 1810</ref>, <date date="2005-08-08">Aug. 8, 2005</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/119/1126">119 Stat. 1126</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
